Enum AsmVisitor.MateStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AsmVisitor.MateStatus>
      • org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.ca.asm.AsmVisitor.MateStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<AsmVisitor.MateStatus>
    Enclosing interface:
    AsmVisitor

    public static enum AsmVisitor.MateStatus
extends Enum<AsmVisitor.MateStatus>
    MateStatus indicates the relative positioning of the mate of this read in the assembly.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      BAD_LONG
      The pair assembled into one scaffold with the proper orientation but were placed too far apart.
      BAD_SHORT
      The pair assembled into one scaffold with the proper orientation but were placed too close together.
      BOTH_DEGENERATE
      Both reads in the pair were assembled into degenerate unitig.
      BOTH_SINGLETON
      Neither read in the mate pair were assembled
      BOTH_SURROGATE
      Both reads were placed in surrogate unitigs.
      DEGENERATE
      This read's mate was assembled into a degenerate unitig.
      DEPRECATED_BAD
      Deprecated. 
      DIFFERENT_SCAFFOLD
      Each mate was placed in different scaffolds.
      GOOD
      The pair assembled into one scaffold with the proper orientation and within the acceptable distance.
      NO_MATE
      This read has no mate.
      OUTTIE_ORIENTATION
      The pair assembled into one scaffold but in the oriented away from each other.
      SAME_ORIENTATION
      The pair assembled into one scaffold but in the same orientation.
      SINGLETON_MATE
      This read's mate was placed in a singleton unitig.
      SURROGATE 
      UNASSIGNED
      Mate pair was unprocessed by CA pipeline; should never appear.
